## Photos

### How does photo documentation work?

When you take a photo through TradeFrame, it automatically captures the GPS coordinates and timestamp. This metadata is embedded in the photo and can be displayed as a watermark — useful for insurance claims, dispute resolution, or proof-of-work documentation.

### What is the watermark?

The watermark is a small strip at the bottom of each photo showing the date/time, GPS coordinates, job type, and client name. You can toggle watermarking on or off in **Settings → Photo Settings**. You can also toggle between the original and watermarked version when viewing any photo.

### How do voice notes work?

When capturing a photo, tap the microphone icon to record a voice note. TradeFrame uses speech-to-text to transcribe your words in real-time. The transcription is saved with the photo and included in reports. This is useful for quickly noting conditions or details on-site without typing.

### How do annotations work?

Open any photo in the detail view and use the annotation tools to draw directly on the image. You can choose from 7 colors (red, orange, yellow, green, blue, white, black) and adjust the line width. Use this to circle damage, mark areas of concern, or highlight specific details for clients.

### What is Before/After mode?

Before/After mode (Premium) lets you pair two photos together — one taken before the work and one after. From the job detail, tap **Before/After Mode**. You can select existing photos from the job or capture new ones. Paired photos are labeled with orange "Before" and green "After" badges in the gallery.

### Can I adjust photo quality?

Yes. In **Settings → Photo Settings**, use the quality slider to set JPEG compression between 50% and 100%. Higher quality means larger file sizes. The default is 80%.

