## Export (Premium)

### What export formats are available?

- **Jobs CSV** — One row per job with client, type, date, status, estimated/invoiced/paid/outstanding amounts, and photo/estimate/invoice counts.
- **Estimates CSV** — One row per estimate with client, job type, title, status, grand total, and rejection details.
- **Invoices CSV** — One row per invoice with client, job type, invoice number, status, total, paid amount, outstanding, and payment method.
- **Summary PDF** — A printable report with aggregate statistics, job listings, and rejection analysis.

### Where can I import the CSV files?

The CSV files are compatible with QuickBooks, Excel, Google Sheets, and any accounting or spreadsheet software that reads CSV format.

### How do I export?

Go to the **Analytics** tab, set your desired filters, then scroll to the **Export Data** section. Tap **Export All** for the full package (3 CSVs + PDF) or **Jobs CSV** for just the job data. The share sheet will open so you can save, email, or AirDrop the files.

