## Troubleshooting

### My financial numbers look wrong. What should I do?

Navigate away from the screen and come back. TradeFrame refreshes all financial data when you open the Analytics, Job Detail, or Client Detail views. If numbers still seem off, check that your invoices have the correct status — an invoice marked "Paid" without a recorded payment will count its full total as revenue.

### An estimate shows as "Pending" but the job is done.

This shouldn't happen with the current version. Estimates on Complete or Archived jobs are automatically treated as "Won" in the pipeline. If you see this, try opening the job and toggling the status to another value and back to Complete.

### I don't see my notifications.

Check **Settings → Notifications** in TradeFrame to make sure the relevant type is toggled on. Then check iOS Settings → TradeFrame → Notifications to make sure system-level permissions are granted with alerts and banners enabled.

### Photos aren't showing GPS data.

Make sure Location Services are enabled for TradeFrame in iOS Settings → Privacy & Security → Location Services. TradeFrame needs "While Using" access to tag photos with coordinates.

### Export isn't working.

Make sure you have at least one job in the filtered date range. The export buttons are disabled when there's no data to export. Check your date range filters at the top of the Analytics view.

